Deltaville was first listed as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusVA/>

The [[Census Bureau]] defines Deltaville as a [[census-designated place]] (CDP) with a population of 1,119 as of 2010.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2010 |title=Virginia Trend Report 2: State and Complete Places |url=https://mcdc.missouri.edu/webrepts/pl94trends/Virginia_stplace2.html |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120711160933/http://mcdc.missouri.edu/webrepts/pl94trends/Virginia_stplace2.html |archive-date=2012-07-11 |website=mcdc.missouri.edu}}</ref> As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 Census]], the town had a population of 1,057. According the 2020 Census as well, Deltaville has a 42.9% [[Employment-to-population ratio|employment rate]], a [[median income]] $66,905 with a 6.1% [[poverty rate]], and a total of 1,188 houses with 394 occupied by families. Of the population, 927 are white, 37 are mixed, 29 are black, 27 are Hispanic, 8 are Native American, 3 are Asian, and 8 are other. 33% of the population is 65 years old or older.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Deltaville CDP, Virginia |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Deltaville_CDP,_Virginia?g=160XX00US5122064 |access-date=2024-05-27 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

